ture and can lead to the stabilisation of polar rather than antipolar order</gtr:description><gtr:exploitationPathways>The findings have been published major international journals with high impact factor and have bee presented as part of plenary and invited talks at major international conferences</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>74AC4898-D414-446F-8CF4-D7E88D5E8801</gtr:id><gtr:outcomeId>r-9463929580.025317763bc3c</gtr:outcomeId><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Aerospace, Defence and Marine,Electronics</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication><gtr:id>5E5AFD62-5B06-45A9-916F-D2CA6DE138F4</gtr:id><gtr:title>A family of oxide ion conductors based on the ferroelectric perovskite Na0.5Bi0.5TiO3.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Nature materials</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/person/00fdefe91ff283a2134de1284108f187"><gtr:id>00fdefe91ff283a2134de1284108f187</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Li M</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2014-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>1476-1122</gtr:issn><gtr:outcomeId>55ee84a63572c6.74639157</gtr:outcomeId></gtr:publication><gtr:publication><gtr:id>4CFD374F-4D4D-4342-A98B-6D726CD9A588</gtr:id><gtr:title>The atomic structure and chemistry of Fe-rich steps on antiphase boundaries in Ti-doped Bi
 
